cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CV, cs.SI

The paper proposes a novel approach for ensemble clustering of high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper focuses on incorporating subspaces and diversified metrics to address the curse of dimensionality. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DM (Data Mining). Additionally, the paper uses image and speech datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
